-- Turkish Stocks: Ford Otomotiv, Yapi Kredi, Yapi Kredi Sigorta
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-01-19T16:50:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/turkish-stocks-ford-otomotiv-yapi-kredi-yapi-kredi-sigorta.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index  gained 0.4 percent to 54,607.89 at the close in Istanbul,
rising for a fourth day.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO)   fell 2.5 percent to
17.45 liras. Ford Motor Co.’s production unit in Turkey aims to
sell 128,000 vehicles in Turkey this year, according to chief
executive Nuri Otay, speaking in Istanbul today, down from
141,633 last year.  Yapi & Kredi Bankasi AS  (YKBNK TI), the bank part-owned by
UniCredit SpA and  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL) , surged 5.2 percent to 3.05
liras as UniCredit surged as much as 17 percent before
tomorrow’s deadline for trading the rights to its stock sale.
The Italian lender is raising the money to plug a capital
shortfall and comply with the European Banking Authority’s
targets.  Yapi Kredi Sigorta AS (YKSGR)   shares jumped 6.8 percent
to 13.40 liras, the biggest jump in nine months. Zurich
Insurance Co. Ltd. offered to buy the insurance unit owned by
Yapi Kredi, according to a report in Haberturk newspaper. Yapi
Kredi denied it’s trying to sell the company in a filing with
the stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
